    "summary": "As a specialist in agrohydrology and soil physics I work at Wageningen Environmental Research (WENR) and have a position as research associate at the University of Bristol (UK).\n\nAt WENR I focus on unsaturated zone modelling in combination with data processing and data analysis techniques including sensitivity analysis, model parameter calibration, data assimilation, digital twins, AI.\n\nAt the University of Bristol I still work on the topic of my long finished PhD: the CosmicRay Neutron Sensor (CRNS). This novel soil moisture sensor technique is used in hydrological and land surface interaction process studies. I cooperate with different researchers in the UK and Germany.\n\nSkills: perseverance, solving complex problems, processing, analysing and presenting complex data, (agro)hydrological/soil physical modelling, programming, multidisciplinary project management\n\nFloorball (team sport; sort of hockey), yoga, mountainbike, running (bootcamp)",
